    "As expected, adaptation was robustly present in all ROIs (Figure 2A); p < 0.025, d ≥ 0.98; all effect sizes and p-values are listed in Supplementary Table S1; all p values listed in the results section are corrected for multiple comparisons -see Figure legends for more information).We then examined whether, as predicted by with our second hypothesis, omission responses occurred in subcortical pathways.",
    "In agreement with the hypothesis, we observed stronger BOLD responses to unexpected omission om4 than to repeated tones std1 in all auditory ROIs (Figure 2B).",
